The Zondo Commission will hear State Security Agency (SSA) related evidence from the Former Chairperson of the High-Level Review Panel into the State Security Agency, Dr Sydney Mufamadi. * Editor's note: This livestream courtesy #DStv403. JOHANNESBURG - Former safety and security minister Sydney Mufamadi is expected to testify at the state capture inquiry on Monday. The commission is focusing on State Security Agency-related evidence. READ: State capture inquiry to resume Mufamadi is also the former chairperson of the government's high-level review panel which was appointed in June 2018 by President Cyril Ramaphosa. In 2019, a report on the SSA found that there had been 'political malpurposing and factionalisation of the intelligence community over the past decade or more'.